{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839977147,"sessionID":"ses_287b1b427ffe9laVG8H8tx72KC","part":{"id":"prt_d784f9ea40014uKWmHVV0XlkMQ","messageID":"msg_d784f12440016IUCZOJtXygeuX","sessionID":"ses_287b1b427ffe9laVG8H8tx72KC","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-140ce0093f2e4f92a493cd9e53ae8ef8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","oldString":"## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n| AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n| Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |","newString":"## Alternatives Considered\n\n| Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|-------------|------|------|----------|\n| **Inline Template (corev1.PodSpec)** | Direct reuse of Kubernetes types, familiar API | Too permissive, includes fields not relevant to code interpreters (init containers, volumes, etc.) | Rejected |\n| **Separate WarmPool CRD** | Decoupled warm pool lifecycle management | Adds complexity, warm pool is tightly coupled to interpreter spec | Rejected |\n| **AuthMode as string (no enum)** | Flexible for future modes | No validation, prone to typos | Rejected - use typed enum |\n| **Embed SandboxTemplate from AgentRuntime** | Code reuse, consistency | Different requirements (AgentRuntime uses full PodSpec, CodeInterpreter needs lighter template) | Rejected - use dedicated CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate |\n| **Status with multiple condition types** | Rich status reporting | Over-engineering for S-size task | Rejected - keep simple with Conditions + Ready |\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n| AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n| Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md\n@@ -67,8 +67,18 @@\n | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers |\n | Workload Manager | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim instances from CodeInterpreter specs |\n | Router | Routes code interpreter requests to appropriate sandboxes |\n \n+## Alternatives Considered\n+\n+| Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n+|-------------|------|------|----------|\n+| **Inline Template (corev1.PodSpec)** | Direct reuse of Kubernetes types, familiar API | Too permissive, includes fields not relevant to code interpreters (init containers, volumes, etc.) | Rejected |\n+| **Separate WarmPool CRD** | Decoupled warm pool lifecycle management | Adds complexity, warm pool is tightly coupled to interpreter spec | Rejected |\n+| **AuthMode as string (no enum)** | Flexible for future modes | No validation, prone to typos | Rejected - use typed enum |\n+| **Embed SandboxTemplate from AgentRuntime** | Code reuse, consistency | Different requirements (AgentRuntime uses full PodSpec, CodeInterpreter needs lighter template) | Rejected - use dedicated CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate |\n+| **Status with multiple condition types** | Rich status reporting | Over-engineering for S-size task | Rejected - keep simple with Conditions + Ready |\n+\n ## Risks\n \n | Risk | Mitigation |\n |------|------------|\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","before":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n\n1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n| Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n\n### Type Definitions Required\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n\n```\nCodeInterpreter\n├── Spec\n│   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n│   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n│   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n│   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n│   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n│   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n├── Status\n│   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n│   └── Ready (*bool)\n└── List: CodeInterpreterList\n```\n\n#### Supporting Types\n\n- `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, imagePullPolicy, imagePullSecrets\n- `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none authentication modes\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n- Webhook validation logic\n- CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n- client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n- AgentRuntime CRD (handled in AR-001)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n| `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for PodSpec elements (EnvVar, PullPolicy, ResourceRequirements) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers |\n| Workload Manager | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim instances from CodeInterpreter specs |\n| Router | Routes code interpreter requests to appropriate sandboxes |\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n| AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n| Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header\n2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions\n3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply validation markers for required fields and enums\n4. **Printer Columns**: Add Age column for `kubectl get` output\n\n## References\n\n- Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/","after":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n\n1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n| Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n\n### Type Definitions Required\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n\n```\nCodeInterpreter\n├── Spec\n│   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n│   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n│   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n│   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n│   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n│   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n├── Status\n│   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n│   └── Ready (*bool)\n└── List: CodeInterpreterList\n```\n\n#### Supporting Types\n\n- `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, imagePullPolicy, imagePullSecrets\n- `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none authentication modes\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n- Webhook validation logic\n- CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n- client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n- AgentRuntime CRD (handled in AR-001)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n| `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for PodSpec elements (EnvVar, PullPolicy, ResourceRequirements) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers |\n| Workload Manager | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim instances from CodeInterpreter specs |\n| Router | Routes code interpreter requests to appropriate sandboxes |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n| Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|-------------|------|------|----------|\n| **Inline Template (corev1.PodSpec)** | Direct reuse of Kubernetes types, familiar API | Too permissive, includes fields not relevant to code interpreters (init containers, volumes, etc.) | Rejected |\n| **Separate WarmPool CRD** | Decoupled warm pool lifecycle management | Adds complexity, warm pool is tightly coupled to interpreter spec | Rejected |\n| **AuthMode as string (no enum)** | Flexible for future modes | No validation, prone to typos | Rejected - use typed enum |\n| **Embed SandboxTemplate from AgentRuntime** | Code reuse, consistency | Different requirements (AgentRuntime uses full PodSpec, CodeInterpreter needs lighter template) | Rejected - use dedicated CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate |\n| **Status with multiple condition types** | Rich status reporting | Over-engineering for S-size task | Rejected - keep simple with Conditions + Ready |\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n| AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n| Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header\n2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions\n3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply validation markers for required fields and enums\n4. **Printer Columns**: Add Age column for `kubectl get` output\n\n## References\n\n- Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/","additions":10,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839977131,"end":1775839977145}}}}
